## 2. Push to GitHub
Follow the GitHub steps from before to get your code into a repo.

## 3. Deploy on Railway
1. Go to [railway.app](https://railway.app) and sign in with GitHub
2. Click **"New Project"** → **"Deploy from GitHub repo"**
3. Select your `runners-weather` repo
4. Click **"Add Variable"** and add:
   - Key: `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`
   - Value: your Anthropic API key
5. Railway auto-detects Node and deploys — takes about 1 minute

## 4. Get your URL
Once deployed, go to **Settings → Networking → Generate Domain** and Railway gives you a URL like `https://runners-weather.up.railway.app`. Your Join39 endpoint would be:
```
https://runners-weather.up.railway.app/api/weather